history.content: One of my friends took 61C + 16B + 188 and was definitely doable.  I know on draft schedule 161 will not be offered in spring 2021, but you need 61C to take 161.

children.subject: 188 has lower workload but harder exam. I don't advise you to take 61c and 161 concurrently
Would you consider 188 and 161 to be of equivalent difficulty? I am planning on taking 61C and 161 concurrently.

probably doable, garcia 61c is a pretty manageable workload & i honestly don't think ee16b is that bad. 161 is also not too high workload -- just work hard on the projects. i think the biggest danger will be potentially having 61c & 161 projects due the same week, but if you're used to 3 techs you should be fine with this schedule.

It would be very doable if you are not also doing full time recruitment. Applying and Interview will take a lot of time and effort especially in this situation. I personal don’t think that you should take 3 techs in the Fall. Get a job first then you can take all of classes in your last semester.

history.content:
I’m a rising senior and planning on recruiting for full time offers this fall. I’m done with all my requirements and just need 61C and 16B to graduate but heard from a lot of people that you should take 161.

Is this schedule doable to do while recruiting? I am considering taking 161 PNP if this is a difficult courseload.
